## Architecture Overview

VPN007 deploys multiple anti-censorship VPN services on a single VM, orchestrated
by Docker Compose. Traffic is obfuscated behind standard HTTPS ports using a
two-layer routing architecture:

### Two-Layer Routing Diagram

```
Internet Traffic (ports 443/tcp{% if enable_port_8443 %}, 8443/tcp{% endif %})
        │
        ▼
┌─────────────────────────────┐
│   nftables Firewall         │
│   (default-deny, AS/subnet  │
│    blocking, SSH allow)      │
└──────────┬──────────────────┘
           │
           ▼
┌─────────────────────────────┐
│  Layer 4: Nginx Stream      │
│  (SNI-based routing)        │
│                             │
│  SNI={{ reality_sni }}      │──► Xray (VLESS+Reality) — raw TCP proxy
│  SNI={{ domain }}           │──► Nginx HTTP (L7)
└──────────┬──────────────────┘
           │
           ▼
┌─────────────────────────────┐
│  Layer 7: Nginx HTTP        │
│  (TLS termination +         │
│   path-based routing)       │
│                             │
│  {{ xui_path_prefix }}/*    │──► 3x-ui Web Panel (IP-restricted)
│  {{ awg_panel_path_prefix }}/* │──► AmneziaWG Panel (IP-restricted)
│  /* (default)               │──► Cover Site
└─────────────────────────────┘
```

**Layer 4 (Nginx stream):** Inspects the SNI field in the TLS ClientHello without
decrypting. Reality-destined traffic (SNI `{{ reality_sni }}`) is proxied directly
to Xray. All other traffic goes to the Nginx HTTP block.

**Layer 7 (Nginx HTTP):** Terminates TLS using ACME certificates, then routes
requests by URL path to backend services. Unmatched requests are served by the
cover site{% if cover_site_url %} (proxying `{{ cover_site_url }}`){% endif %}.

