## Firewall

The deployment provisions a complete nftables firewall with:

- **Default-deny** inbound policy
- **Allowed inbound ports:**
  - 443/tcp (HTTPS)
{% if enable_port_8443 %}
  - 8443/tcp (secondary HTTPS)
{% endif %}
  - {{ awg_listen_port or "configured" }}/udp (AmneziaWG)
  - 22/tcp from approved SSH IPs only
  - 80/tcp opened dynamically during certbot renewal only
- **AS/subnet blocking** via nftables named sets (`blocked_v4`, `blocked_v6`)
{% if blocked_as_numbers %}
  - Blocked AS numbers: {{ blocked_as_numbers | join(", ") }}
{% endif %}
{% if blocked_subnets %}
  - Blocked subnets: {{ blocked_subnets | join(", ") }}
{% endif %}
- **Bidirectional blocking** — rules apply to both inbound and outbound traffic
- **Panel access restriction** — enforced at the Nginx level via `allow`/`deny` directives

### Firewall Management

```bash
# View current ruleset
sudo nft list ruleset

# View blocked IP sets
sudo nft list set inet filter blocked_v4
sudo nft list set inet filter blocked_v6

# Reload firewall rules
sudo nft -f /etc/nftables.conf
```

