## Systemd Timers

The deployment installs the following systemd timers:

| Timer | Interval | Purpose |
|-------|----------|---------|
| `blocklist-updater.timer` | Every {{ blocklist_update_interval_hours }} hours | Re-resolves AS numbers to IP prefixes and updates nftables blocked sets |
| `hostname-resolver.timer` | Every {{ hostname_resolve_interval_min }} minutes | Re-resolves approved hostnames to IPs and updates Nginx panel access list |
| `certbot-renew.timer` | Twice daily (certbot default) | Renews TLS certificates via Let's Encrypt |

### Managing Timers

```bash
# Check timer status
systemctl list-timers --all

# View specific timer
systemctl status blocklist-updater.timer

# View timer logs
journalctl -u blocklist-updater.service

# Manually trigger a timer
systemctl start blocklist-updater.service
```

